# Technical Specification: Real-Time Notification System

---

## Overview

This document specifies the design for a real-time notification system that supports push, email, and in-app delivery channels.

[TOC:2-3]

## Requirements

### Functional Requirements

1. Send notifications in real time (under 500ms latency)
2. Support multiple delivery channels
3. Allow users to configure notification preferences
4. Batch similar notifications to prevent flooding

### Non-Functional Requirements

- Handle 10,000 notifications per second at peak
- 99.9% delivery rate
- Maximum 2-second end-to-end latency

## Architecture

::: architecture-diagram
```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Event Source] --> B[Message Queue]
    B --> C[Notification Service]
    C --> D[Push Channel]
    C --> E[Email Channel]
    C --> F[In-App Channel]
```
:::

## Data Model

| Field | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| id | UUID | Unique notification ID |
| user_id | UUID | Target user |
| channel | ENUM | push, email, in_app |
| payload | JSONB | Notification content |
| status | ENUM | pending, sent, failed, read |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | Creation time |
| sent_at | TIMESTAMP | Delivery time |

Table: Notifications table schema {#notifications-table}

## API Design

### Send Notification

```json
{
  "user_id": "usr_abc123",
  "template": "order_shipped",
  "channels": ["push", "email"],
  "data": {
    "order_id": "ord_456",
    "tracking_url": "https://track.example.com/456"
  }
}
```

### Notification Preferences

```json
{
  "user_id": "usr_abc123",
  "preferences": {
    "order_updates": ["push", "email"],
    "marketing": ["email"],
    "security_alerts": ["push", "email", "in_app"]
  }
}
```

## Error Handling

W> Failed notifications must be retried with exponential backoff.
W> After 3 failed attempts, move to a dead letter queue.

N> Log all delivery failures with full context for debugging.

## Implementation Plan

- [x] Design data model
